  m_Name: 3_Singleton_Data
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Title: Singleton
  m_TextPages:
  - "The <b>singleton pattern</b> guarantees a class has just one globally accessible
    instance. The pattern ensures a single, static instance by eliminating duplicates.\n\nThe
    AudioManager in this scene is a generic <b>Singleton</b>. \n\nClick the mouse
    to play the sound."
  - "Use the <b>AudioManager.Instance</b> to access a centralized manager for playing
    sound effects.\r\n\r\nThe singleton pattern ensures that any duplicates are removed
    from the scene. This can help manage global access to a resource \u2014 in this
    case, an audio system."
  - "Click the screen to play a specific AudioClip with custom variations using the
    <b>AudioManager.Instance</b>.\n\nSingletons can be useful for maintaining performance
    and consistency for central managers or resources. \n\nA <b>PersistentSingleton</b>
    works across different scenes, maintaining state and behavior throughout various
    parts of an application."
  m_CurrentIndex: 0
  m_AdditionalText: Enable the singleton to remove duplicates.
  m_FooterText: 'Press <b>R</b> to reset the scene. '
